Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 400
degrees. Trim @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce}, then halve lengthwise through stem
ends. Peel @Sweet Potatoes{3}, then cut into ½-inch cubes. Mince @Parsley{¼%ounce}.
Halve @Blood Orange{1}, then squeeze juice into a #small bowl{}.

Toss Brussels sprouts on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of
@Vegetable Oil{1%tablespoon}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Roast in oven
until lightly crisped, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: Arrange the Brussels sprouts cut-side down to help them cook and crisp evenly.

Place sweet potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 1
inch. Bring to a boil. Cook until tender, about ~{12%minutes}. Drain thoroughly,
then return to #pot{}. Add @Brown Sugar{1%tablespoon} and
@Butter{1%tablespoon}. Mash with a #potato masher{} or fork until smooth.
Season with salt and pepper. Keep covered off heat until meal is ready.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Season
@New York Strip Steak{12%ounce} all over with salt and pepper. Add to pan and
cook to desired doneness, ~{2-5%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside
to rest on a #plate{} for at least ~{5%minutes}.

Carefully pour out any excess grease in pan used for steak, then return to stove
over medium-high heat. Stir in @water{½%cup}, orange juice, @Rosemary{1%sprig}
(use the rest as you like), and @Beef Demi-Glace{1}. Bring to a boil, then lower
heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add @Butter{1%tablespoon} and
half the parsley, stirring to melt butter. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide sweet potatoes between plates. Toss Brussels sprouts with half the
@Dried Cranberries{½%ounce} (use the rest as you like) and divide between plates.
Stir any juices released by steak into sauce in pan; discard rosemary sprig.
Divide steak between plates and drizzle with sauce. Garnish with remaining
parsley.